    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Canara Bank Capital India. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Senior Financial Analyst to strengthen our Surat-based team.\n\nAbout Canara Bank Capital India:\nCanara Bank Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in SQL\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Learning & development budget\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Surat, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Canara Bank Capital India!",
